# Anti-AI Website Rules

Never generate template-based sections. The site must feel like a luxury digital experience — not a yoga instructor portfolio.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Large hero + 3 cards + testimonials + CTA
- Generic wellness stock photos
- Everything centered
- Predictable/repeated layouts
- Too much text visible at once
- Cookie-cutter animations
- Heading → Text → Button stacked repeatedly
- Service card grids on the homepage
- Testimonial sliders

## Required Approach

- **Asymmetrical compositions** — every major section has a unique visual structure
- **Mix layouts:** full-width imagery, editorial, split-screen, layered typography, immersive video, horizontal storytelling
- **Section uniqueness** — never repeat the same card/panel pattern twice on one page

| Section | Layout |
|---------|--------|
| Hero | Video-first, huge typography, floating sound-wave viz |
| About | Editorial magazine, full-screen portrait, timeline |
| Nervous System | Interactive scroll — stress states calm visually |
| Services | Apple-style immersive numbered panels (NOT cards) |
| Corporate | Dark immersive, large metrics |
| Retreats | Horizontal scrolling documentary |
| Testimonials | Polaroid wall, staggered, discovered feel |
| Contact | Architectural minimalism, vast whitespace |

## Awwwards Test (mandatory before every page/section)

1. Would this look out of place on a premium Awwwards site? → **Redesign**
2. Does it resemble a template or typical yoga website? → **Redesign**
3. Does it feel AI-generated? → **Redesign**

## Design Inspiration

Aman Resorts · Apple · Linear · Arc Browser · Patagonia Stories · Kinfolk · Aesop

Principles: minimal but emotional · spacious but intentional · sophisticated typography · cinematic imagery · slow interactions

